// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Data source: Sefaria. "Tanach with Text Only" = Leningrad Codex text
// stripped of nikkud (vowel points) and cantillation — the correct edition
// for a raw word-frequency count, since points/accents are pronunciation
// marks, not part of the word.
//
// Two network sources are tried, in order:
//  1. Sefaria's public API (sends CORS headers, built for browser use)
//  2. Sefaria's public export bucket (a CLI/server-oriented mirror; some
//     networks block direct browser access to it)
// If both are unreachable, the person can load the same files manually
// from their device — see the file picker in the error state below.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// TEST-ONLY CONTROL. Shows a manual Base/Student switcher in the header
// for testing the entitlement gating (Print, ads) without real billing.
// Set to false to hide it, or delete the header block that reads this
// flag entirely, before publishing to any app store.
const SHOW_TEST_CONTROLS = true;

// Bundled English translation (JPS 1917/1985 public-domain text, from Sefaria's
// export), keyed by the same "Book Chapter:Verse" citation used throughout the
// app. Ships with the app so the Verse Detail page's English Translation
// section works instantly and offline, with the live Sefaria fetch and manual
